A vintage-style illustration of a craftsman's wooden workbench viewed from above, featuring neatly organized compartments and small wooden boxes with hinged lids, each containing different colorful components like gears, springs, and small mechanical parts. The compartments are arranged in a grid pattern with decorative carved borders around each section. Warm amber lighting casts soft shadows across the weathered wood grain. Scattered around the main boxes are tiny brass hinges, small labels, and a worn leather tool roll partially unrolled at the edge. The color palette emphasizes rich browns, warm oranges, and aged brass tones with a sepia-tinted atmosphere reminiscent of early 20th century workshop photography.
